<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>She recently announced she was leaving Essex to 'prioritise her life' with fiancé Bradley Dack. </p>

<p>And Olivia Attwood put on a leggy display as she stepped out in Manchester in a figure-hugging black dress and heeled over-the-knee boots on Thursday.  </p>

<p>The former Love Islander, 29, showcased her gym-honed physique in the ensemble which featured striking neon green detailing for the outing at Menagerie Restaurant &amp; Bar. </p>

<p>Wow: Olivia Attwood, 29, put on a leggy display as she stepped out in Manchester in a figure-hugging black dress and heeled over-the-knee boots on Thursday</p>

<p>She turned up the glam with a £3,450 black matte Dior handbag and accessorised with gold earrings, reading 'f***' and 'off', as she filmed for her ITVBe show - Olivia Meets Her Match. </p>

<p>The reality star styled her blonde locks in loose waves and pinned half up in a sweet ponytail to accentuate her pretty features. </p>

<p>Olivia highlighted her sun-kissed glow with a dash of bronzer over her cheekbones and a full, fluttery eyelashes for the outing. </p>

<p>Beauty: The reality star styled her blonde locks in loose waves and pinned half up in a sweet ponytail to accentuate her pretty features</p>

<p>Chic: Olivia highlighted her sun-kissed glow with a dash of bronzer and turned up the glam with a £3,450 black matte Dior handbag</p>

<p>Star: The former Love Islander showcased her gym-honed physique in the ensemble which featured neon green detailing </p>

<p>It comes after Olivia shocked her TOWIE castmates during Wednesday night's episode by finally making the decision to leave Essex and 'prioritise' being with Bradley. </p>

<p>During the show the blonde beauty explained how she was feeling conflicted about spending so much time away from her beau and being with the girls in Essex. </p>

<p>Revealing her decision at the end of the show, Olivia said: 'I've got everything I've ever wanted waiting in Manchester, a whole life I'm missing out on. </p>

<p>'These last few weeks saying I feel conflicted and feel I've come to realisation i need to be up there a bit more permanently. It's the right thing to do, it's just sad isn't it.'</p>

<p>Time to go: Speaking about her decision to go to Bradley on TOWIE, Olivia said: 'I've got everything I've ever wanted waiting in Manchester, a whole life I'm missing out on'</p>

<p>Olivia's revelation left Nicole Bass and Clelia Theodorou in shock with the former Love Islander having to tell them to not cry and struggling not to give them a hug, which she couldn't do due to social distancing rules.</p>

<p>Nicole could be seen getting emotion as she said: 'It's so hard. I'm happy for your future but I'm gonna miss you so much.' </p>

<p>Before walking away, Olivia said: 'The last year has been amazing, so many highs and some of the best times of life. Some people are going to miss me, and some not so much. </p>

<p>'But I know who I am and I've got pals for life. So girls, there's no time like the present. I'm gonna leave now before any more drama starts.'    </p>

<p>Cute couple: Olivia's new eight-episode series will follow Olivia and her Blackburn Rovers footballer fiancé Bradley, 26, as they plan their wedding and buy their first home in Cheshire</p>
